{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Scz8ugfttbKKzYEDiucp5","type":"tool_result","content":"[open] Issue #33: Auth-gated Get Pro pricing CTA\n  Author: @luiscipparrone1\n  Status: OPEN\n  URL: https://github.com/synergyio1/locus-landing-page/issues/33\n\n  Description:\n    ## Parent PRD\n    \n    #29\n    \n    ## What to build\n    \n    Wire the pricing **Get Pro** CTA to the auth state and Stripe checkout.\n    \n    Server pages (`/` and `/pricing`) read the current user from Supabase and pass `isAuthed` down through the `Pricing` section to the Pro plan card. The Pro CTA becomes a small client component that branches on `isAuthed`:\n    \n    - Logged out → renders an anchor to `/login?next={pathname+hash}&notice=signin`. After the user signs in, they land back on the pricing surface they came from. A second click — now authenticated — proceeds to checkout.\n    - Logged in → renders a button that calls the shared `startCheckout` helper (#31) with the cadence currently selected in the toggle. Pending state flips the label to \"Redirecting…\"; failures render an inline error.\n    \n    A new pure helper, `buildLoginNext(pathname, hash)`, composes the `next` query value at click time. Output must round-trip through the existing `sanitizeNext` on the login page. The Free plan CTA is unchanged.\n    \n    ## Acceptance criteria\n    \n    - [ ] As a logged-out user on the homepage, clicking **Get Pro** navigates to `/login?next=/%23pricing&notice=signin` (or equivalent encoding) and the login page shows the \"Please sign in\" banner.\n    - [ ] As a logged-out user on `/pricing`, clicking **Get Pro** navigates to `/login?next=/pricing&notice=signin`.\n    - [ ] After logging in, the user lands back on the pricing surface they came from (homepage `#pricing` or `/pricing`).\n    - [ ] A second click on **Get Pro** while authenticated starts Stripe Checkout for the cadence currently selected in the toggle (monthly or yearly).\n    - [ ] As a logged-in user, the first click on **Get Pro** starts Stripe Checkout immediately, without a login detour.\n    - [ ] The CTA shows pending feedback and renders an inline error on failure.\n    - [ ] The Free plan CTA still links to `/download` in both auth states.\n    - [ ] `buildLoginNext` is unit-tested for homepage hash, `/pricing`, paths with query strings, and malformed inputs; outputs pass `sanitizeNext`.\n    - [ ] Pricing renders an anchor for the Pro CTA when `isAuthed=false` and a button when `isAuthed=true`; covered by tests.\n    - [ ] No new server routes are introduced; no changes to the existing checkout API, Stripe webhook, or billing portal route.\n    \n    ## Blocked by\n    \n    - Blocked by #30\n    - Blocked by #31\n    \n    ## User stories addressed\n    \n    - User stories 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 23, 25","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27f26790-1c77-48bd-8a91-2b53cecc1231","uuid":"7ce8f7b4-8bc3-4af3-912e-f80057294b86","timestamp":"2026-04-28T13:38:04.168Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"[open] Issue #33: Auth-gated Get Pro pricing CTA\n  Author: @luiscipparrone1\n  Status: OPEN\n  URL: https://github.com/synergyio1/locus-landing-page/issues/33\n\n  Description:\n    ## Parent PRD\n    \n    #29\n    \n    ## What to build\n    \n    Wire the pricing **Get Pro** CTA to the auth state and Stripe checkout.\n    \n    Server pages (`/` and `/pricing`) read the current user from Supabase and pass `isAuthed` down through the `Pricing` section to the Pro plan card. The Pro CTA becomes a small client component that branches on `isAuthed`:\n    \n    - Logged out → renders an anchor to `/login?next={pathname+hash}&notice=signin`. After the user signs in, they land back on the pricing surface they came from. A second click — now authenticated — proceeds to checkout.\n    - Logged in → renders a button that calls the shared `startCheckout` helper (#31) with the cadence currently selected in the toggle. Pending state flips the label to \"Redirecting…\"; failures render an inline error.\n    \n    A new pure helper, `buildLoginNext(pathname, hash)`, composes the `next` query value at click time. Output must round-trip through the existing `sanitizeNext` on the login page. The Free plan CTA is unchanged.\n    \n    ## Acceptance criteria\n    \n    - [ ] As a logged-out user on the homepage, clicking **Get Pro** navigates to `/login?next=/%23pricing&notice=signin` (or equivalent encoding) and the login page shows the \"Please sign in\" banner.\n    - [ ] As a logged-out user on `/pricing`, clicking **Get Pro** navigates to `/login?next=/pricing&notice=signin`.\n    - [ ] After logging in, the user lands back on the pricing surface they came from (homepage `#pricing` or `/pricing`).\n    - [ ] A second click on **Get Pro** while authenticated starts Stripe Checkout for the cadence currently selected in the toggle (monthly or yearly).\n    - [ ] As a logged-in user, the first click on **Get Pro** starts Stripe Checkout immediately, without a login detour.\n    - [ ] The CTA shows pending feedback and renders an inline error on failure.\n    - [ ] The Free plan CTA still links to `/download` in both auth states.\n    - [ ] `buildLoginNext` is unit-tested for homepage hash, `/pricing`, paths with query strings, and malformed inputs; outputs pass `sanitizeNext`.\n    - [ ] Pricing renders an anchor for the Pro CTA when `isAuthed=false` and a button when `isAuthed=true`; covered by tests.\n    - [ ] No new server routes are introduced; no changes to the existing checkout API, Stripe webhook, or billing portal route.\n    \n    ## Blocked by\n    \n    - Blocked by #30\n    - Blocked by #31\n    \n    ## User stories addressed\n    \n    - User stories 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 23, 25","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
